## 2. Bluetooth Extension — Adding HC-05

```
Arduino Uno                  HC-05 Bluetooth Module
───────────                  ──────────────────────
   Pin 0 (RX)  ◄──────────   TX
   Pin 1 (TX)  ──────────►   RX  (use 1kΩ + 2kΩ voltage divider)
   5V          ──────────►   VCC
   GND         ──────────►   GND
```

> ⚠️ The HC-05 RX pin operates at 3.3V logic. Use a voltage divider (1kΩ and 2kΩ resistors) between Arduino TX (5V) and HC-05 RX to avoid damaging the module.

---

## 3. Key Pin Summary

| Signal | Arduino Pin | Connected To |
|---|---|---|
| Soil moisture reading | A0 | Sensor AOUT |
| Relay control | D2 | Relay IN |
| Bluetooth TX (data out) | D1 (TX) | HC-05 RX |
| Bluetooth RX (commands in) | D0 (RX) | HC-05 TX |
| Power | 5V | All modules VCC |
| Ground | GND | All modules GND |

---

## 4. Moisture Threshold Values

| Sensor Reading (Raw) | Condition |
|---|---|
| ~300 (thresholdMin) | Very wet soil |
| ~800 (thresholdMax) | Very dry soil |
| Mapped < 40% | Relay ON → Valve opens |
| Mapped ≥ 40% | Relay OFF → Valve closed |

Adjust `thresholdMin`, `thresholdMax`, and the `sensorValue < 40` threshold in the code to match your specific soil type and sensor.
